cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.MM 

This paper deals with depth estimation from single monocular images, which is a common problem in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves supervised learning and the use of deep neural networks, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper proposes a new dataset and a new approach to depth estimation, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of stereo videos and stereo matching algorithms could also suggest a connection to cs.RO (Robotics) or cs.MM (Multimedia).
